pageContext.claim: “Yes, as I understand it, before I got here, $7.5 million in 2014 [was given by the Obama administration to the Wuhan, China, lab associated with the coronavirus outbreak]. And look, they said they were studying different things, and you know, things like that happen. But you know, money was given by the Obama administration early on.”
pageContext.analysis: This is false, according to FactCheck.org: "The lab received only $600,000 through a five-year grant to EcoHealth Alliance, a grant that spanned both the Obama and Trump administrations and had been renewed last year [2019]."
